<br>
Give me a chance to recover and I'll tell you the works. Basically I think Jared got his picture made with everyone at the show. He was hanging out with all the tallent. We both got several lessons from the noteables is Lefty, Mel Krieger, Joan Wulff, the Rajeffs, etc. Lori Ann rode back from the show to Jackson with us in the air plane. I gave about 100 casting lessons. My personal highlight of the show was when I asked Jason Borger if I could take some video of him casting and he actually knew who I was.<br>
<br>
By the way I got casting video of almost everyone there. Lots of really good footage of some various styles. The only two that I wish I would have gotten were Bruce Richards and Jerry Seim. I did however get some footage of a German fella casting 65 feet with just using his hands and no rod. That's pretty interesting.<br>
<br>
I can certianly tell you all that the new Loomis rods were the HIT of the show. The Loomis booth was PACKED!! You guys have got to cast these rods. The new Stream Dance series is without a doubt the best rod I have ever cast. I know Denver makes anyone a casting hero but I personally compared them with all the other rods. Also, I have to say that I like the new Xi2 from Sage. Galvan has a new larger reel out that I'm curious about trying. Most of the manufacturers are not really going out on a limb right now with new gear. Most of what I saw was shoring up their old designs.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 6:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Sounds like ya'll had a good time.  I'll bet your happy to be back.  Did you get my e-mail about the boat?<br>
